# Costroid is developed on Linux/WSL (LF). Several committed data files are compared
# BYTE-FOR-BYTE in golden tests (e.g. crates/costroid-core/tests/v12_round_trip_golden.rs)
# and/or are sha256-pinned (scripts/check_{power_profiles,pricing_snapshots,benchmarks}.sh).
# They MUST check out with LF on every OS — otherwise Windows `core.autocrlf` rewrites the
# LF blobs to CRLF on checkout and the golden/integrity checks fail. `eol=lf` overrides
# autocrlf unconditionally. (Caught by M6 cross-OS CI: the v1.2→v1.3 round-trip golden.)
*.csv    text eol=lf
*.json   text eol=lf
*.jsonl  text eol=lf
*.sha256 text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never line-ending-normalized.
*.ttf    binary
*.otf    binary
*.woff   binary
*.woff2  binary
*.png    binary
*.gif    binary
*.ico    binary
